EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to animals; authorizing the governing body of
certain counties and incorporated cities to establish a
program to waive the adoption fee of certain animals
adopted by a person who is a veteran, law enforcement
officer or first responder; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes a board of county commissioners and city council to
2 exercise certain powers relating to the control of animals. (NRS 244.359, 266.325)
3 Sections 1 and 2 of this bill authorize the governing body of a county or
4 incorporated city, respectively, that owns and operates an animal shelter, or
5 appropriates money to an animal shelter, to establish a program to waive the
6 adoption fee of certain animals adopted by a person who is a veteran, law
7 enforcement officer or first responder.
8 Sections 1 and 2 require that, if established, these programs: (1) waive the
9 adoption fee for not more than one eligible animal from the animal shelter for a
10 period of 6 months for each veteran, law enforcement officer or first responder who
11 adopts an animal; (2) require such a veteran, law enforcement officer or first
12 responder to provide a valid form of identification; (3) require the animal shelter to
13 report to the governing body of the county or city, as applicable, certain
14 information concerning the program; and (4) require the animal shelter to maintain
