1 Section 1. Chapter 244 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. If a county owns and operates an animal shelter or the
4 board of county commissioners appropriates money to an animal
5 shelter to provide care and shelter to animals, the board of county
6 commissioners may establish a program to waive the adoption fee
7 of an animal that is 6 months or older, has been at the animal
8 shelter for at least 7 consecutive days and is adopted from the
9 animal shelter by a person who is a veteran, law enforcement
10 officer or first responder.
11 2. A program established pursuant to subsection 1 must:
12 (a) Waive the adoption fee for not more than one animal that
13 meets the requirements of subsection 1 for a period of 6 months
14 for each veteran, law enforcement officer or first responder who
15 adopts such an animal from the animal shelter;
16 (b) Require a veteran, law enforcement officer or first
17 responder who wishes to adopt an animal under the program to
18 present a valid form of identification that confirms that he or she
19 is a veteran, law enforcement officer or first responder;
20 (c) Report to the board of county commissioners the number of
21 animals adopted under the program and whether each animal was
22 adopted by a veteran, law enforcement officer or first responder;
23 and
24 (d) Require the animal shelter to maintain records of each
25 adoption made under the program.
26 3. On or before October 1 of each even-numbered year after
27 the board of county commissioners establishes a program
28 pursuant to subsection 1, the board of county commissioners shall
29 submit a report to the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau
30 for transmittal to the next regular session of the Legislature that
31 includes the number of animals adopted under a program
32 established pursuant to subsection 1 and whether each animal was
33 adopted by a veteran, law enforcement officer or first responder.
